works</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/giuse/machine_learning_workbench\">machine_learning_workbench</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/giuse/machine_learning_workbench\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">13</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":13,\"repo\":\"giuse/machine_learning_workbench\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> -\nGrowing machine learning framework written in pure Ruby, high performance computing using\n<a href=\"https://github.com/ruby-numo/\">Numo</a>, CUDA bindings through <a href=\"https://github.com/sonots/cumo\">Cumo</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/sonots/cumo\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">86</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":86,\"repo\":\"sonots/cumo\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->.\nCurrently implementating neural networks, evolutionary strategies, vector quantization, and plenty of\nexamples and utilities.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-14T17:15:58.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"arbox/machine-learning-with-ruby","categoryHTML":"<h2>Machine Learning Libraries</h2><h3>Frameworks</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/giuse/DNE\">Deep NeuroEvolution</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/giuse/DNE\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">123</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":123,\"repo\":\"giuse/DNE\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> -\nExperimental setup based on the <a href=\"https://github.com/giuse/machine_learning_workbench\">machine_learning_workbench</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/giuse/machine_learning_workbench\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">13</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":13,\"repo\":\"giuse/machine_learning_workbench\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->\ntowards searching for deep neural networks (rather than training) using evolutionary algorithms. Applications to the\n<a href=\"https://github.com/openai/gym\">OpenAI Gym</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/openai/gym\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">24.1k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":24136,\"repo\":\"openai/gym\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> using <a href=\"https://github.com/mrkn/pycall.rb\">PyCall</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/mrkn/pycall.rb\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">780</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":780,\"repo\":\"mrkn/pycall.rb\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-14T17:15:58.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"arbox/machine-learning-with-ruby","categoryHTML":"<h2>Machine Learning Libraries</h2><h3>Neural networks</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/giuse/machine_learning_workbench/tree/master/lib/machine_learning_workbench/neural_network\">machine_learning_workbench</a> -\nFramework including pure-Ruby implementation of both feed-forward and recurrent neural networks\n(fully connected). Training available using neuroevolution (Natural Evolution Strategies algorithms).</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-14T17:15:58.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"arbox/machine-learning-with-ruby","categoryHTML":"<h2>Machine Learning Libraries</h2><h3>Evolutionary algorithms</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/giuse/machine_learning_workbench/tree/master/lib/machine_learning_workbench/optimizer/natural_evolution_strategies\">machine_learning_workbench</a> -\nFramework including pure-Ruby implementations of Natural Evolution Strategy algorithms\n(black-box optimization), specifically Exponential NES (XNES),\nSeparable NES (sNES), Block-Diagonal NES (BDNES) and more.\nApplications include neural network search/training (neuroevolution).</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-14T17:15:58.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"thangchung/awesome-dotnet-core","categoryHTML":"<h2>Frameworks, Libraries and Tools</h2><h3>Mail</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/cmendible/netDumbster\">netDumbster</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/cmendible/netDumbster\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">88</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":88,\"repo\":\"cmendible/netDumbster\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - a .Net Fake SMTP Server used for testing. Clone of the popular Dumbster.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-14T12:16:50.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"thangchung/awesome-dotnet-core","categoryHTML":"<h2>Frameworks, Libraries and Tools</h2><h3>Serialization</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/JoshClose/CsvHelper\">CsvHelper</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/JoshClose/CsvHelper\" style=\"text-decoration:no