, Transpilers and Languages</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Testura/Testura.Code\">Testura.Code</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Testura/Testura.Code\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">192</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":192,\"repo\":\"Testura/Testura.Code\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Wrapper around the Roslyn API and used for generation, saving and compiling C# code. It provides methods and helpers to generate classes, methods, statements and expressions.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-14T02:30:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ironcev/awesome-roslyn","categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Projects</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/antiufo/roslyn-linq-rewrite\">roslyn-linq-rewrite</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/antiufo/roslyn-linq-rewrite\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">684</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":684,\"repo\":\"antiufo/roslyn-linq-rewrite\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Compiles C# code by first rewriting the syntax trees of LINQ expressions using plain procedural code. This increases performance by minimizes heap allocations and dynamic dispatch.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-14T02:00:20.000Z"}]}},"pageContext":{"type":"day","from":1523664000000,"to":1523750399999,"previousId":"2018-04-15","nextId":"2018-04-13","nextName":"Apr 13th, 2018","previousName":"Apr 15th, 2018"}},"staticQueryHashes":["228695001","2744905544","3289010534"]}